These are used to aggregate data of many records into a single record.This Function are mainly used with the group by clause or
where clause.


1. Sum{}
It totals numerical values of given attribute.

Example: Select sum (salary) from employ;

2.Avg{}
It is used to calculate average of the numerical values of the given attribute.

Syntax:
select Avg(salary) from employ;

3. Max{}
It returns the highest value of the given attribute.

4. Min{}
It returns the lowest value of the given attribute.
Eg: select min (salary) from employ;

5. Count{}
It returns the total number of not null values fro the given attribute.

6. Count{*}
The COUNT(*) function counts the total rows in the table, including the NULL values.


